In [17]:
# Group iostat by timestamp and aggregate disk metrics
iostat_agg = iostat_df.groupby(iostat_df.index).agg({
    'tps': 'mean',
    'kB_read': 'sum',
    'kB_wrtn': 'sum',
    'service_time': 'mean'
}).fillna(0)

# Group netstat by timestamp and aggregate network metrics
netstat_agg = netstat_df.groupby(netstat_df.index).agg({
    'ipkts': 'sum',
    'ierrs': 'sum',
    'opkts': 'sum',
    'oerrs': 'sum',
    'coll': 'sum'
}).fillna(0)
In [18]:
# Aggregate process data - calculate total CPU and memory by timestamp
process_agg = process_df.groupby(process_df.index).agg({
    'cpu': 'sum',
    'mem': 'sum'
}).fillna(0)
In [20]:
# Merge all dataframes on timestamp
merged_df = vmstat_df.join(iostat_agg, how='outer')
merged_df = merged_df.join(netstat_agg, how='outer')
merged_df = merged_df.join(process_agg, how='outer')

# Handle missing values
merged_df = merged_df.fillna(method='ffill').fillna(method='bfill')

6. Resource Usage Classification¶

In [47]:
# Define classification labels based on system metrics
def create_resource_labels(df):
    """Create resource usage labels based on system metrics"""
    labels = np.zeros(len(df))
    
    # Normal: CPU < 70%, Memory < 70%
    # High load: CPU >= 70% OR Memory >= 70%
    # Critical: CPU >= 90% AND Memory >= 80%
    
    labels[(df['cpu'] < 70) & (df['mem'] < 70)] = 0  # Normal
    labels[(df['cpu'] >= 70) | (df['mem'] >= 70)] = 1  # High load
    labels[(df['cpu'] >= 90) & (df['mem'] >= 80)] = 2  # Critical
    
    return labels
